Descripción del trabajo:
Company DescriptionDo you want beneficial technologies being shaped by your ideas? Whether in the areas of mobility solutions, consumer goods, industrial technology or energy and building technology - with us, you will have the change to improve quality of life all across the globe. Welcome to Bosch!We are a pacesetter and trendsetter in the field of steering systems for passenger cars and commercial vehicles. Bends, switchbacks, parking spaces, rough roads, slippery road surfaces and sudden lane-change manoeuvres – this is our world. We call it the fascination of steering. We set the course for technological change and are a highly capable, experienced partner for the automotive industry.Job DescriptionThe Logistics Innovation, Process and Packaging Supervisor is mainly responsible for coordinate and also supports technology, logistics' processes and packaging development improvement projects and change management activities within the value stream. This position interacts regularly with employees, management, senior management, customers and suppliers. The level of quality and accuracy displayed in the performance of this job will have an impact on the daily operations of the department and, ultimately, customer satisfaction. Detailed Description:• Plan and implement extensive innovation logistics projects as part of a strategic role of logistics in collaboration with internal/external departments;
• Observe, analyze, and evaluate innovative logistics processes on the market and derive optimal solutions for his/her own area;
• Analyze existing logistics processes and formulate alternative possible solutions. Perform cost-effectiveness analyses, cost comparisons and propose improvement ideas; 
• Responsible to coordinate and hands on support LOG management to LOG-C, LOG-Q function and design and automate logistics reporting (internal and external);  
• Implementation of standardized and automated LOG processes tools; Selection of IT tools to automate LOG and key user role support to LOG processes;
• Coordinate and hands on packaging development process for cost improvements and new plant projects to assure successful lunches;
• Lead innovation initiatives inside LOG and support BPS process implementation in all Log areas;
• Active role in digitalization strategy inside and outside logistics area;QualificationsBachelor Degree - Supply Chain Management, Logistics Management, Engineering, Economics, International Trade, etc.Desired Master's DegreeLanguage:English- Advanced levelGerman- Desired (Optional)Experience in a similar role >5 yearsTechnical Skills:ERP (SAP). - Advanced (Desired)Microsoft Office (Excel, PPT, Power BI) - IntermediateAutomation tools (ej. Catalytic) - BasicWorking Knowledge of in logistics and/or manufacturing - AdvancedSoft Skills:Market / Customer OrientationCooperationNegotiations skillsInterdisciplinary ThinkingProblem SolvingSelf-drivenLeadership, ability to take risks, manage projects and convince peopleGood logical thinking and critical analysisInnovation and technology passionateProblem solution oriented Systemic visionCustomer orientedResilience in complex and dynamic environments towards internal and external customers
